## 1. Grant Without Fee (Free Uses)

You may use, copy, modify, and distribute this software **without paying** the
author, **provided all of the following are true**:

(a) **Non-commercial use**. You are not charging money, in any form, for any
product or service that incorporates this software. Examples still considered
free-of-charge:
  - Personal projects, portfolios, blogs
  - Academic / research / teaching use
  - Non-profit organizations
  - Organizations with revenue < USD $1M/year AND headcount < 10 employees,
    using Mentor as an internal tool
  - Public forks for learning, demo, issue submissions, PR contributions

(b) **Preserve attribution**. Every copy or derivative work must include:
  - This LICENSE file in full
  - The original copyright line above
  - A clear notice of any modifications you made

(c) **Source-visible**. If you distribute a binary or hosted version, you must
also make the corresponding source code (your modified version) available free
of charge, with the same attribution.

